<HTML>
<TITLE>
An example lesson
</TITLE>
<BODY>
<h1> Overview </h1>
Welcome to the lesson.  This is just a simple lesson to demonstrate
how one can embed self-assessments in a lesson with text.
<a NAME="lesson1">

(SELF-ASSESSMENT TITLE) Try the first self-assessment.
(SELF-ASSESSMENT START)

(RETURN-TO-WHERE) 
  <a href="http://www.cs.jcu.edu.au/~curtis/htmls/software/lesson.html#lesson1">
  Back to the lesson.
  </a>
(QUESTIONS)
(QUESTIONSET)
(MC) Using the primitive and composite type notation developed in class,
what is the following C type?
<P>
  <code>
     type value = 3;
  </code>
<P>
 
(r) integer
(w) float
(w) integer X float
(w) integer + float
(w) integer --> float
(w) none of the above
(h) It is a simple type.
(e) Recall that a type is a set of values (and associated operations
on those values).

(MC) Using the primitive and composite type notation developed in class,
what is the following Pascal type?
<P>
<code>
   type value = real;
</code>
<P>
(w) integer
(r) float
(w) integer X float
(w) integer + float
(w) integer --> float
(r) none of the above
(h) It is a simple type.
(e) Reals are actually implemented by floating point numbers.
(SELF-ASSESSMENT END)


